The paper deals with the private information retrieval (PIR) problem, which is a topic in information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the capacity-achieving codes, which are related to error-correcting codes, and the upload cost, which is related to communication complexity. Hence, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible sub-categories.
